To create your own private website that will shred files by just entering a URL, you would need to:

Set up a web server: Use a service like AWS, DigitalOcean, or even a local server.
Build the frontend: Create a simple HTML form that allows users to input a URL.
Build the backend: Write server-side code to handle the URL input, download the file, and delete it securely.
Ensure security: Implement authentication and secure file handling to prevent unauthorized access.
Deploy the website: Host your website on a private server or cloud service.
